> [4] https://try.github.io/levels/1/challenges/1
> [5] http://git-scm.com/book/en/v2

I was forced to start using git as some of the open source projects I 
work on switched to using it for maintaining their public code 
repositories. Git is different enough from the other VCS' I have used 
that it drove me batty at first. With git I often wound up with my 
checked out code "not on a branch". I've lost code changes I was working 
on while using git. That never happened while using any of the 
RCS/CVS/SVN tools. Eventually I started to get a bit of a handle on git 
and created my own cheat sheet for it.

I have made it available via the wiki on my website. The URL is
http://www.ve3syb.ca/wiki/doku.php/docs:git_survivors_guide

-- 

Cheers!

Kevin.

