> I haven't dealt with the problems of large files in git, but I've
> heard it's ugly, so this is interesting.  I'm curious if more
> experienced git users actually think this is a good idea.

Well for one it certainly breaks the idea that the git tree is self
contained.

I think it is a solution trying to solve a problem that should be solved
some other way.

Perhaps some files are so huge they don't have any reason to be stored
in your code tree.  They may need a better designed storage system of
their own.

So I don't get it, and don't think it fits the git model at all (then
again I don't think github does either for that matter).

